{"id":18560,"title":"[Anthrax meningoencephalitis: a case following a cutaneous lesion in Morocco].","abstract":"Anthrax meningoencephalitis is very rare especially following skin location. We report a case of meningoencephalitis secondary to skin lesion. The diagnosis is based on clinical presentation and confirmed by microbiological tests. Its evolution remains fatal despite aggressive resuscitation.","date":"2014-06-14","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24784916","annotations":[{"name":"Microbiology","weight":0.735174,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microbiology"},{"name":"Cutaneous conditions","weight":0.727341,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cutaneous_conditions"},{"name":"Skin","weight":0.665105,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.633471,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.59533,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Morocco","weight":0.209824,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morocco"},{"name":"Cardiopulmonary resuscitation","weight":0.126224,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardiopulmonary_resuscitation"},{"name":"Anthrax","weight":0.121905,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthrax"},{"name":"Evolution","weight":0.106224,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolution"},{"name":"Aggression","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aggression"},{"name":"Meningoencephalitis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meningoencephalitis"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"},{"name":"Secondary school","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secondary_school"},{"name":"Presentation","weight":0.0147415